# AltaCV tailored resume

Applies when editing `roles/<company-slug>/<role-slug>/resume.md`.

## Facts

- Pull employers, dates, titles, and metrics from `master.md` only — no fabrication
- Tailor into the role folder — never compile `master.md` directly

## Format

- YAML front matter at top; header via `\makecvheader` — no `# Name` markdown title
- Job entries: `**Org — Title** · *dates | location*`
- Education: plain markdown — not job-line format
- Sub-sections: `**Name**` alone on a line → `\cvsubsection`
- **Technical Skills:** bullet list — one `- **Category:**` line per group (see `roles/anthropic/applied-ai-architect/resume.md`)
- Output is AltaCV markdown → PDF via `./template/build.sh`

## Do not

- Use generic ATS headings (`# NAME`, `## PROFESSIONAL SUMMARY`) — incompatible with this pipeline
- Edit `template/` (LaTeX, `job.lua`, `altacv.cls`) unless explicitly requested
- Use tectonic, generic pandoc PDF engines, or removed root `make` targets
- Create single-level `roles/<combined-slug>/` folders — use two-level layout

## Full mapping

See `.cursor/plans/altacv_style_workflow/00-CONTEXT.md` and `DESIGN.md`.

## Language

UK English.
